# Car Mechanic Shop Portfolio

**Stack:** React · TypeScript · Tailwind CSS · TanStack Router · TanStack Form

A portfolio website for a car mechanic shop. Trustworthy, professional, grounded — not sterile corporate. Industrial-refined aesthetic with dark tones, metallic accents, one bold signature accent color.

## TypeScript — Strict, No Exceptions

- `"strict": true` in tsconfig. Always.
- **`any` is banned.** No `any`, no `as any`, not "temporarily." Use `unknown` + type guards.
- Event handlers are fully typed: `React.MouseEvent<HTMLButtonElement>`, `React.ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>`, etc.
- Use `enum` for finite sets (routes, categories, variants, statuses). Use `const` for static values.

## Zero Magic Strings or Numbers

Every repeated string or number must be a constant or enum. Never hardcode string literals or numeric values in components.

```ts
// constants/routes.ts
export enum AppRoute { HOME = "/", SERVICES = "/services", ABOUT = "/about", CONTACT = "/contact" }

// constants/ui.ts
export const ANIMATION_DURATION_MS = 300;
export const MAX_CONTENT_WIDTH = "max-w-7xl";

// constants/content.ts
export const COMPANY_NAME = "AutoPro Garage";
export const PHONE_NUMBER = "+30 210 123 4567";
```

## Code Quality

- No `console.log` — use a proper logger or remove before commit.
- No commented-out code committed to the codebase.
- No `!important` in Tailwind or CSS.
- No inline styles (`style={{}}`).
- No prop drilling past 2 levels — use composition or context.

## Environment Variables

- All env vars prefixed with `VITE_`. Access via `import.meta.env.VITE_*`.
- `.env.example` committed (blank values). `.env.local` gitignored.
- Typed helper in `lib/env.ts` validates at startup.

## Hard Rules — Quick Reference

| Category | Rule |
|---|---|
| TypeScript | `any` banned — no exceptions |
| Styling | No inline styles, no arbitrary Tailwind values (`p-[17px]`), no margin, no grid unless flex can't do it, no `!important` |
| Components | Max 600 lines per file, no `<div>` for interactive elements |
| Code quality | No `console.log`, no magic strings/numbers, no commented-out code |
| i18n | No hardcoded user-facing strings, every component has translation files |
| Accessibility | Zero axe critical/serious violations, no removed focus outlines |
| SEO | Every page has `<title>` and `<meta description>` |
| Routing | No hardcoded paths — use type-safe `<Link>` |
| Responsive | No horizontal scroll on any viewport |
| Dependencies | Check bundlephobia before installing |
| Git | Conventional commit messages, all commits pass lint + type-check |
